com.intel.icecp.core.security

Class CryptoProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intel.icecp.core.security.CryptoProvider

  • public class CryptoProvider
extends Object
    Main entry point to retrieve cryptographic services. This class (lazily) loads the available cryptographic tools (using SecurityServices), and provides getter methods to retrieve them.

        public static SignatureScheme getSignatureScheme(String name,
                                                 boolean force)
                                          throws UnsupportedSignatureAlgorithmException
        Returns an instance of the (already loaded) service implementing the signature scheme identified by the supplied name; throws an exception if this cannot be found or instantiated
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the signature scheme wanted
        force - Forces service loading (e.g., to be used when new services are added at runtime by a module)
        Returns:
        An instance of the requested service
        Throws:
        UnsupportedSignatureAlgorithmException - If the given scheme is not supported or a new instance can not be created
